%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693362be71107c9f34577a05%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222792%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJohnny%20C.%20Taylor%20Jr.%3Cp%3EArun%20Sankar%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%20has%20fought%20an%20ex-staffer%20over%20discrimination%20claims%20since%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20a%20Colorado%20jury%20issued%20a%20%2411.5%20million%20verdict%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20former%20employee.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrm-johnny-taylor-dei-workplace-lawsuits-layoffs-2025-11%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESHRM%20has%20been%20embroiled%20in%20controversies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20recently%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20jury%20on%20Friday%20issued%20an%20%2411.5%20million%20verdict%20against%20the%20world's%20largest%20HR%20organization%20over%20allegations%20it%20had%20racially%20discriminated%20and%20retaliated%20against%20a%20former%20employee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%2C%20known%20as%20SHRM%2C%20was%20found%20liable%20for%20racial%20discrimination%20and%20retaliation%20and%20hit%20with%20a%20ruling%20of%20%241.5%20million%20in%20compensatory%20damages%20and%20%2410%20million%20for%20punitive%20damages%2C%20according%20to%20Ariel%20DeFazio%2C%20a%20lawyer%20for%20the%20plaintiff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESHRM%20said%20it%20plans%20to%20appeal%20the%20decision.%20%26quot%3BToday's%20decision%20does%20not%20reflect%20the%20facts%2C%20the%20law%2C%20or%20the%20truth%20of%20how%20SHRM%20operates%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shrm.org%2Fabout%2Fpress-room%2Fshrm-statement-on-mohamed-lawsuit-ruling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrade%20group%20said%20in%20a%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20acted%20with%20integrity%2C%20transparency%2C%20and%20in%20full%20alignment%20with%20our%20values%20and%20obligations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESHRM%20was%20sued%20in%202022%20by%20Rehab%20Mohamed%2C%20who%20worked%20at%20the%20trade%20group%20as%20an%20instructional%20designer%20from%202016%20to%202020.%20The%20case%20was%20tried%20over%20the%20course%20of%20five%20days%20in%20a%20Colorado%20federal%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20optics%20are%20bad%20because%20they've%20held%20themselves%20out%20as%20an%20authority%20on%20best%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Alice%20K.%20Jump%2C%20an%20employment%20attorney%20and%20partner%20at%20law%20firm%20Reavis%20Page%20Jump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMohamed%20said%20in%20her%20suit%20that%20she%20was%20racially%20discriminated%20against%20by%20a%20white%20supervisor%20and%20faced%20retaliation%20for%20complaining%20to%20management.%20She%20said%20she%20raised%20concerns%20about%20racial%20discrimination%20and%20retaliation%20with%20leadership%2C%20including%20SHRM's%20CEO%2C%20Johnny%20C.%20Taylor%20Jr.%2C%20and%20its%20head%20of%20human%20resources%2C%20throughout%20the%20summer%20of%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20testifying%20on%20December%204%2C%20Taylor%20said%20he%20wasn't%20involved%20in%20Mohamed's%20termination.%20A%20former%20SHRM%20employee%2C%20Mike%20Jackson%2C%20who%20said%20he%20was%20responsible%20for%20investigating%20the%20matter%2C%20told%20the%20court%20that%20Mohamed's%20was%20the%20only%20discrimination%20claim%20he%20had%20ever%20investigated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20questions%20from%20Hunter%20Swain%2C%20another%20of%20Mohamed's%20lawyers%2C%20Jackson%20said%20that%20he%20left%20SHRM%20in%202021%20and%20his%20title%20was%20manager%20of%20employee%20experience.%20He%20said%20he%20became%20a%20certified%20HR%20professional%20while%20employed%20there%20and%20that%20he%20had%20undergone%20one%20training%20session%20on%20HR%20investigations%20just%20a%20few%20months%20before%20the%20discriminatory%20events%20that%20Mohamed%20cited%20in%20her%20lawsuit%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20by%20Swain%20what%20he%20learned%20from%20the%20training%2C%20Jackson%20said%20he%20couldn't%20remember%20any%20specifics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESHRM%20has%20consistently%20denied%20Mohamed's%20claims.%20In%20September%2C%20SHRM%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20bar%20Mohamed%20from%20introducing%20evidence%20or%20argument%20that%20the%20organization%20is%20a%20specialist%20in%20HR%20best%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20month%2C%20US%20District%20Judge%20Gordon%20P.%20Gallagher%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrm-discrimination-case-hr-expertise-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edenied%20SHRM's%20request%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20its%20%26quot%3Basserted%20expertise%20in%20human%20resources%20is%20integral%20to%20the%20circumstances%20of%20this%20case%20and%20cannot%20reasonably%20be%20excluded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20testimony%2C%20Taylor%20said%20SHRM's%20work%20includes%20advising%20HR%20professionals%20about%20best%20practices%2C%20including%20those%20pertaining%20to%20investigating%20internal%20complaints%20of%20discrimination%20and%20retaliation.%20He%20said%20SHRM%20has%20a%20set%20of%20curricula%20around%20best%20practices%20for%20investigating%20employment%20complaints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20verdict%20was%20not%20surprising%20given%20that%20SHRM%20promotes%20itself%20as%20an%20expert%20in%20HR%2C%20Boston%20employment%20lawyer%20Evan%20Fray-Witzer%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20be%20held%20to%20a%20higher%20standard%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20SHRM%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrm-johnny-taylor-dei-workplace-lawsuits-layoffs-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eembroiled%20in%20various%20controversies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20recently%20reported.%20These%20include%20a%20new%20attendance%20policy%20that%20penalizes%20workers%20who%20arrive%20even%20a%20minute%20after%209%20a.m.%3B%20a%20memo%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Bconservative%26quot%3B%20dress%20code%20that%20bans%20sequins%3B%20and%20a%20companywide%20meeting%20in%20which%20Taylor%20said%20some%20staffers%20were%20%26quot%3Bentitled%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bcomplacent%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bsloppy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20pre-trial%20discovery%20for%20Mohamed's%20case%2C%20SHRM%20revealed%20the%20existence%20of%20two%20other%20discrimination%20complaints%20from%20employees.%20One%20case%2C%20filed%20with%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission%20in%202018%2C%20was%20settled.%20The%20other%2C%20filed%20with%20a%20California%20regulator%20in%202021%2C%20is%20pending.%20SHRM%20also%20denied%20wrongdoing%20in%20those%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20very%20happy%20that%20the%20jury%20spent%20a%20week%20listening%20very%20closely%20to%20the%20evidence%20and%20that%20they%20decided%2C%20as%20a%20result%2C%20to%20hold%20SHRM%20accountable%2C%26quot%3B%20Mohamed's%20lawyer%2C%20DeFazio%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20She%20said%20the%20verdict%20would%20%26quot%3Bsend%20a%20message%20to%20workplaces%20in%20the%20entire%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrm-discrimination-lawsuit-verdict-11-million-racism-retaliation%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1764980375000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F693362f07ecd1d1da663119b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrm-discrimination-lawsuit-verdict-11-million-racism-retaliation%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20jury%20found%20the%20HR%20trade%20organization%20liable%20for%20racial%20discrimination%20and%20retaliation%20against%20a%20former%20employee.%22%